parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping and failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and strand the driver. It can also lead to costly repairs and replacement of the transmission.
Torque converter failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and strand the driver. It can also lead to costly repairs and replacement of the torque converter.
Vehicle movement while in park can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle rolling or moving forward while in park
even with the parking brake engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Odometer failure can lead to inaccurate mileage readings, which can affect the vehicle's resale value and maintenance schedules.
Failure of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, loss of control, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to engage or disengage
the vehicle does not slow down when the brakes are applied
the cruise control system is stuck in reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the speed control deactivation switch can cause unintended acceleration, loss of control, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The speed control deactivation switch fails to disconnect
the vehicle does not slow down when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Throttle sticking or sudden acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the vehicle does not slow down when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed or incomplete recall repairs can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, leading to accidents and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Dealerships do not have parts available for recall repairs
recall repairs are incomplete or delayed
owners are not notified of recall repairs.

brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause vibration when braking, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
